#variety of features 
candidate_features = [
    "Jitter_rel", "Jitter_abs", "Jitter_RAP", "Jitter_PPQ",
    "Shim_loc", "Shim_dB",
    "NHR", "HNR",
    "RPDE", "DFA", "PPE",
    "Delta1", "Delta4", "Delta8", "Delta12"
]

features = [f for f in candidate_features if f in df.columns]
print("\nUsing these features for plots:\n", features)

Using these features for plots:
 ['Jitter_rel', 'Jitter_abs', 'Jitter_RAP', 'Jitter_PPQ', 'Shim_loc', 'Shim_dB', 'RPDE', 'DFA', 'PPE', 'Delta1', 'Delta4', 'Delta8', 'Delta12']
In[29]:
#boxplot:feature vs status 
for feat in features:
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    sns.boxplot(data=df, x="Status", y=feat)
    plt.title(f"{feat} by Status (0 = Control, 1 = Parkinson's)")
    plt.xlabel("Status")
    plt.ylabel(feat)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
In[31]:
#Histograms: distrbution by status 
for feat in features:
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    sns.histplot(data=df, x=feat, hue="Status", kde=True, element="step")
    plt.title(f"Distribution of {feat} by Status")
    plt.xlabel(feat)
    plt.ylabel("Count")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
